1
00:00:02,550 --> 00:00:03,910
(Seo Hyun Jin)

2
00:00:05,180 --> 00:00:07,250
(Yoo Jae Myung)

3
00:00:07,950 --> 00:00:10,550
(Lee Si Woo)

4
00:00:17,530 --> 00:00:19,500
(Yoon Se A)

5
00:00:27,170 --> 00:00:28,170
(Chang Ryul)

6
00:00:35,010 --> 00:00:36,680
(Dahyun)

7
00:00:41,850 --> 00:00:46,890
(Love Me)

8
00:01:26,190 --> 00:01:27,190
Dad's heading out.

9
00:01:27,560 --> 00:01:28,920
Okay.

10
00:01:31,490 --> 00:01:32,960
Feed Oscar for me.

11
00:01:38,970 --> 00:01:41,270
All right, you have fun.

12
00:01:46,210 --> 00:01:47,610
Oscar, why are you so down?

13
00:01:49,850 --> 00:01:50,850
Are you hungry?

14
00:02:07,130 --> 00:02:08,130
Daniel, you...

15
00:02:12,230 --> 00:02:13,940
Oscar's food...

16
00:02:24,410 --> 00:02:25,680
I don't like her.

17
00:02:34,390 --> 00:02:35,390
Dad.

18
00:02:39,690 --> 00:02:41,430
Can't you break up with her?

19
00:02:50,340 --> 00:02:51,340
If you don't,

20
00:02:56,550 --> 00:02:58,080
maybe I should go back to Mom's?

21
00:03:09,860 --> 00:03:14,330
I used to feel so tired but fulfilled after my shift.

22
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:17,230
I've been walking on eggshells around the director.

23
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:19,000
It feels uneasy.

24
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:21,840
I know, right? We have so few expecting mothers.

25
00:03:22,100 --> 00:03:23,810
I've been enjoying the downtime, actually.

26
00:03:24,510 --> 00:03:28,780
Hey, if you're not busy, that means we're overstaffed.

27
00:03:29,980 --> 00:03:30,980
Especially us.

28
00:03:32,250 --> 00:03:35,180
I'm feeling kind of blah, and I've got so much pent-up energy.

29
00:03:35,980 --> 00:03:37,220
What do you say we go out for a team dinner?

30
00:03:37,550 --> 00:03:38,749
- Sounds great!
- I'm in!

31
00:03:38,750 --> 00:03:40,389
- Count me in.
- So where are we going?

32
00:03:40,390 --> 00:03:42,890
- I'm feeling grilled intestines.
- What? I'm craving lamb skewers.

33
00:03:43,390 --> 00:03:45,030
- How many rounds are we going for?
- Hi, Do Hyun.

34
00:03:45,090 --> 00:03:47,530
- At least three rounds!
- Then lamb skewers for round one.

35
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:49,800
- What?
- Yes, I just got off work.

36
00:03:50,530 --> 00:03:51,530
Sashimi sounds good too.

37
00:03:52,070 --> 00:03:54,700
- Do Hyun, are you drunk this early?
- What's going on?

38
00:03:55,370 --> 00:03:56,400
This is bad.

39
00:04:23,870 --> 00:04:24,870
Do Hyun.

40
00:04:41,420 --> 00:04:42,420
Are you okay?

41
00:04:49,090 --> 00:04:50,090
I'm sorry.

42
00:04:54,400 --> 00:04:55,930
Want to walk for a bit?

43
00:05:08,440 --> 00:05:09,580
"I'm fine."

44
00:05:12,410 --> 00:05:13,450
"I'm fine."

45
00:05:16,250 --> 00:05:17,650
All he ever said was "I'm fine."

46
00:05:19,850 --> 00:05:20,860
But...

47
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:23,690
there's no way it could be fine.

48
00:05:24,730 --> 00:05:25,760
That should have been obvious.

49
00:05:29,930 --> 00:05:30,970
I really had no idea.

50
00:05:36,500 --> 00:05:37,970
Of course you wouldn't know.

51
00:05:40,210 --> 00:05:41,580
No one ever knows things like that.

52
00:05:43,710 --> 00:05:46,110
They don't say a word or give any sign...

53
00:05:47,520 --> 00:05:49,920
because they're desperately trying to hide it.

54
00:05:58,430 --> 00:05:59,430
I...

55
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:01,800
want to get along with Daniel.

56
00:06:09,900 --> 00:06:10,910
Why?

57
00:06:11,410 --> 00:06:12,540
You don't think I can?

58
00:06:13,110 --> 00:06:14,110
No.

59
00:06:15,340 --> 00:06:16,340
It's just that...

60
00:06:18,310 --> 00:06:20,420
I don't know what I'm supposed to do.

61
00:06:24,850 --> 00:06:25,890
Let me handle it.

62
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:32,530
Daniel has his own pace and his own way of doing things.

63
00:06:34,330 --> 00:06:37,000
I don't know when that will be or what it will take,

64
00:06:39,830 --> 00:06:42,370
but I'll just have to watch closely for an opening.

65
00:06:44,670 --> 00:06:46,510
And who knows? It might happen sooner than expected.

66
00:07:01,520 --> 00:07:02,620
Seriously, I...

67
00:07:04,860 --> 00:07:05,890
Jun Kyung...

68
00:07:06,830 --> 00:07:08,560
I never expected you to say that.

69
00:07:11,700 --> 00:07:12,830
Daniel's feelings...

70
00:07:13,900 --> 00:07:17,010
I can't control them,

71
00:07:18,940 --> 00:07:20,680
and this is going to be hard on you too.

72
00:07:24,410 --> 00:07:26,110
"What if you decide to leave me?"

73
00:07:27,880 --> 00:07:30,090
"What if you abandon me?" I was worried like that.

74
00:07:33,720 --> 00:07:36,560
Goodness, spoken like a true artist.

75
00:07:37,390 --> 00:07:38,860
So dramatic.

76
00:07:46,230 --> 00:07:48,570
(Catholic Church)

77
00:07:48,640 --> 00:07:51,140
Two single adults, a man and a woman,

78
00:07:51,540 --> 00:07:52,910
spent the night together.

79
00:07:54,080 --> 00:07:55,340
Consensually.

80
00:07:57,680 --> 00:07:59,050
What seems to be the problem?

81
00:08:01,020 --> 00:08:02,020
Well...

82
00:08:04,020 --> 00:08:07,790
- It's not so much a problem...
- Was it just a one-night stand?

83
00:08:07,890 --> 00:08:11,060
No, I wouldn't call it a one-night stand.

84
00:08:11,130 --> 00:08:13,030
Then it's love, I suppose.

85
00:08:14,630 --> 00:08:15,630
Well...

86
00:08:16,160 --> 00:08:19,600
- I wouldn't say it's love...
- Well...

87
00:08:20,900 --> 00:08:25,210
Brother, what is troubling you the most right now?

88
00:08:26,780 --> 00:08:30,280
We first met back in kindergarten, you see.

89
00:08:31,110 --> 00:08:32,110
So?

90
00:08:33,350 --> 00:08:34,350
What I'm trying to say is,

91
00:08:35,250 --> 00:08:39,290
what if this goes wrong and ruins our 20-year friendship?

92
00:08:39,350 --> 00:08:41,890
- That's what I'm worried about.
- So what if it's ruined?

93
00:08:43,890 --> 00:08:44,890
Sorry?

94
00:08:45,660 --> 00:08:49,030
I said, so what if your precious 20-year friendship gets ruined?

95
00:08:51,630 --> 00:08:52,630
Well...

96
00:08:57,310 --> 00:08:59,770
(Parishioner)

97
00:08:59,840 --> 00:09:00,940
It's occupied.

98
00:09:04,810 --> 00:09:06,710
Hey, come on out.

99
00:09:07,950 --> 00:09:08,950
Sorry?

100
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:11,390
I said, come out.

101
00:09:19,860 --> 00:09:22,330
Aren't you a little old to be getting beaten up like this?

102
00:09:23,700 --> 00:09:25,370
I didn't get beaten up, Father.

103
00:09:26,230 --> 00:09:29,200
- This was an act of retribution.
- Good grief.

104
00:09:30,140 --> 00:09:32,810
You really are your father's son, aren't you?

105
00:09:33,810 --> 00:09:34,810
What?

106
00:09:36,340 --> 00:09:38,750
Just drop the "Father." Talk to me like you used to.

107
00:09:41,780 --> 00:09:42,920
All right, Chang Sik.

108
00:09:44,620 --> 00:09:45,620
Right, so...

109
00:09:46,860 --> 00:09:48,920
This is one of those "between love and friendship" things, isn't it?

110
00:09:49,620 --> 00:09:51,160
The classic, boring dilemma.

111
00:09:52,490 --> 00:09:55,360
You can't just sum up our relationship that simply.

112
00:09:56,900 --> 00:09:58,130
Back when we were in school,

113
00:09:58,930 --> 00:10:00,400
you remember what was up with me and Jun Kyung, right?

114
00:10:02,900 --> 00:10:05,270
Could you even call that a "thing"?

115
00:10:06,840 --> 00:10:08,080
If I had to put a label on it,

116
00:10:08,810 --> 00:10:12,910
you chased my uninterested sister and told everyone she was your girl,

117
00:10:13,380 --> 00:10:15,150
until my mom threw a bucket of water on you. That "thing"?

118
00:10:15,220 --> 00:10:17,220
Back in the prime of my passionate youth,

119
00:10:17,450 --> 00:10:20,390
I wonder why I gave up on Jun Kyung, instead of enduring the humiliation.

120
00:10:21,720 --> 00:10:22,720
What?

121
00:10:25,530 --> 00:10:27,430
Back then, I chose friendship.

122
00:10:28,730 --> 00:10:30,930
I was torn between love and friendship.

123
00:10:33,670 --> 00:10:35,840
Yes, right. Some "great friendship" that was.

124
00:10:38,410 --> 00:10:39,410
Hey...

125
00:10:40,010 --> 00:10:42,910
- You were never my sister's type...
- Shut it.

126
00:10:45,450 --> 00:10:47,020
Friendship, my foot.

127
00:10:47,950 --> 00:10:50,180
I just didn't have the courage or the confidence.

128
00:10:51,650 --> 00:10:54,990
It was a loser's excuse, plain and simple.

129
00:10:57,960 --> 00:10:59,360
Are you sure you don't actually like her?

130
00:11:03,970 --> 00:11:05,830
If you don't like her, why are you agonizing over it?

131
00:11:33,490 --> 00:11:35,900
(Editor-in-Chief's Office)

132
00:11:38,530 --> 00:11:40,100
He looks perfectly fine.

133
00:11:42,240 --> 00:11:44,010
Gosh, what a jerk.

134
00:11:45,240 --> 00:11:46,240
Listen up!

135
00:11:47,710 --> 00:11:48,840
I know this is sudden,

136
00:11:49,780 --> 00:11:54,450
but our marketer, Beom Jun, just quit on the spot.

137
00:11:55,680 --> 00:11:57,550
He feels bad for leaving so suddenly so he's treating us all tonight.

138
00:11:57,890 --> 00:11:59,990
Let's all get together after work,

139
00:12:00,420 --> 00:12:02,660
so he can show off how rich he is before he leaves.

140
00:12:03,160 --> 00:12:04,990
He said he's buying the good stuff!

141
00:12:05,490 --> 00:12:07,300
See you all later! I'll treat you to something good!

142
00:12:11,900 --> 00:12:13,170
How cool is that?

143
00:12:13,630 --> 00:12:17,210
Quitting his job for love and heading to Europe indefinitely.

144
00:12:19,010 --> 00:12:22,280
I wish I were your age again, Beom Jun.

145
00:12:22,340 --> 00:12:25,850
Come on, Chief. It's not too late for you.

146
00:12:27,080 --> 00:12:29,850
- I lack the guts and the ability.
- Ability has nothing to do with it.

147
00:12:29,920 --> 00:12:32,390
That's only for guys like him who treat work like a hobby.

148
00:12:32,450 --> 00:12:35,060
So where in Europe are you going?

149
00:12:35,290 --> 00:12:38,590
She said she wanted to visit Estonia,

150
00:12:39,760 --> 00:12:42,000
so I think we'll start with the three Baltic states.

151
00:12:43,660 --> 00:12:46,330
The Baltic states? I've only read about them in books.

152
00:12:47,100 --> 00:12:48,100
Where are the Baltic states?

153
00:12:51,370 --> 00:12:53,040
- So he's really going?
- She's actually going?

154
00:12:53,110 --> 00:12:54,110
Looks like it.

155
00:13:11,630 --> 00:13:15,430
- To think she kept denying it...
- Gosh.

156
00:13:15,500 --> 00:13:18,470
- Just knock it off. Hey, enough.
- Gosh, cake!

157
00:13:19,370 --> 00:13:23,770
Now this is more like it! It's a farewell party, isn't it?

158
00:13:23,840 --> 00:13:24,840
Is that what you went out to buy?

159
00:13:27,840 --> 00:13:28,840
Congratulations.

160
00:13:29,310 --> 00:13:31,780
Enjoy your open-ended Europe trip with your girlfriend.

161
00:13:32,710 --> 00:13:34,280
Goodness, Hye On...

162
00:13:42,660 --> 00:13:43,660
Right.

163
00:13:45,290 --> 00:13:48,260
You're just being true to yourself. I'm the idiot here.

164
00:13:54,340 --> 00:13:55,670
- Wait.
- What's this about?

165
00:13:55,740 --> 00:13:57,210
Wait, why?

166
00:13:57,710 --> 00:14:02,880
(Towel General Trading, Commemorative Towels)

167
00:14:02,980 --> 00:14:07,380
Don't say that! Of course, we can do it for 300 or more.

168
00:14:11,790 --> 00:14:14,990
For crying out loud. Be quiet. I'm on the phone.

169
00:14:15,790 --> 00:14:19,030
No, it's nothing. Yes, please, go ahead. Yes.

170
00:14:19,190 --> 00:14:22,900
We'll take care of that for you. Yes, thank you.

171
00:14:24,900 --> 00:14:25,900
Gosh, Jin Ho!

172
00:14:26,370 --> 00:14:27,570
What brings you here without calling first?

173
00:14:30,040 --> 00:14:31,040
Hey, there.

174
00:14:37,410 --> 00:14:40,150
Yes, sir. I just sent you a text. Did you get it?

175
00:14:40,750 --> 00:14:44,120
Yes, that's right. A hundred each of gray, pink, and white.

176
00:14:44,290 --> 00:14:47,620
Yes, I'll need them by the 15th. All right, thank you.

177
00:14:48,560 --> 00:14:49,720
You have to understand her, Jin Ho.

178
00:14:50,730 --> 00:14:52,390
You know what she's like.

179
00:14:52,760 --> 00:14:55,300
What's wrong with her? She's wonderful.

180
00:14:57,370 --> 00:15:00,200
Wonderful? Did the fiery pit freeze over or something?

181
00:15:01,240 --> 00:15:02,240
A person has to have some...

182
00:15:02,600 --> 00:15:05,010
I'm not asking her to be like a soft, fluffy new towel.

183
00:15:06,440 --> 00:15:09,710
But still, you know? Gosh, she's just so abrasive.

184
00:15:10,140 --> 00:15:11,750
She shouldn't be like an exfoliating towel, at least.

185
00:15:14,050 --> 00:15:15,420
What was that about an exfoliating towel?

186
00:15:15,850 --> 00:15:16,850
You scared me.

187
00:15:18,690 --> 00:15:19,820
When did you get back?

188
00:15:20,290 --> 00:15:22,960
- What about the shop?
- It's empty. Now hurry up and go.

189
00:15:24,060 --> 00:15:25,060
What?

190
00:15:26,960 --> 00:15:27,960
Right.

191
00:15:31,600 --> 00:15:33,300
Jin Ho, I'll come visit you soon.

192
00:15:53,520 --> 00:15:57,730
When my sister brought you home and said you were getting married,

193
00:16:00,030 --> 00:16:03,130
everyone was dead set against it. It was a whole ordeal.

194
00:16:06,400 --> 00:16:08,400
- Can you blame them?
- Right?

195
00:16:08,970 --> 00:16:10,710
Think about how old you two were.

196
00:16:13,140 --> 00:16:16,410
But do you know that I was the only one on your side?

197
00:16:17,140 --> 00:16:18,150
Of course I do.

198
00:16:43,170 --> 00:16:46,140
My sister asked me why I was for it.

199
00:16:46,810 --> 00:16:48,340
What do you think I told her?

200
00:16:52,350 --> 00:16:56,020
I said you seemed so dorky. You'd never be popular with women.

201
00:16:56,080 --> 00:16:59,950
So I was sure you'd never cheat on her.

202
00:17:03,620 --> 00:17:05,730
What am I supposed to say to that right now?

203
00:17:06,030 --> 00:17:08,299
But listen, it's a huge misunderstanding.

204
00:17:08,300 --> 00:17:09,300
- It really is.
- I mean,

205
00:17:09,301 --> 00:17:12,270
while my sister is alive and well,

206
00:17:12,330 --> 00:17:14,370
do you really think you have the guts to cheat on her?

207
00:17:16,440 --> 00:17:17,910
Of course I know you don't.

208
00:17:18,410 --> 00:17:19,410
Right?

209
00:17:23,110 --> 00:17:26,850
I've spent over 20 years living with a man...

210
00:17:27,010 --> 00:17:30,480
who jokes around with people who won't even pay their debts.

211
00:17:32,720 --> 00:17:34,660
Maybe it's because I'm more cynical,

212
00:17:35,390 --> 00:17:38,560
but seeing my husband act like that just drives me crazy.

213
00:17:40,390 --> 00:17:41,460
If...

214
00:17:43,300 --> 00:17:46,370
my husband got into an accident and ended up in that state,

215
00:17:48,500 --> 00:17:51,670
and for seven years, I had to clean up all his messes,

216
00:17:53,440 --> 00:17:55,140
put up with his temper,

217
00:17:56,180 --> 00:17:59,210
and wait on him hand and foot, I...

218
00:18:00,010 --> 00:18:01,750
I could never do it.

219
00:18:04,750 --> 00:18:07,020
But I bet he would do it.

220
00:18:08,620 --> 00:18:09,690
Because he's a fool in that way.

221
00:18:14,560 --> 00:18:16,830
Even though she's my own flesh and blood,

222
00:18:17,600 --> 00:18:19,870
I only thought about how much my poor sister was suffering.

223
00:18:21,140 --> 00:18:22,670
I never considered...

224
00:18:25,240 --> 00:18:27,840
how hard it must have been for you. I'm sorry.

225
00:18:29,340 --> 00:18:30,340
No, it's all right.

226
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:57,300
I still can't bring myself to be happy for you and her.

227
00:18:58,810 --> 00:19:02,740
No, I don't think I ever will be.

228
00:19:06,010 --> 00:19:08,380
You took such good care of my sister.

229
00:19:10,520 --> 00:19:11,690
I was so grateful for that.

230
00:19:15,420 --> 00:19:17,020
I really mean it.

231
00:19:35,440 --> 00:19:38,480
- You should get going!
- Go on! Hurry! Go!

232
00:19:38,750 --> 00:19:40,310
Walk straight, will you? Walk straight!

233
00:19:42,520 --> 00:19:44,150
- Having fun?
- Yes, a blast.

234
00:19:45,220 --> 00:19:46,490
Let's go for round two.

235
00:20:05,840 --> 00:20:07,510
Why are you always here?

236
00:20:09,510 --> 00:20:11,310
Is this the only place you can go?

237
00:20:13,080 --> 00:20:14,450
Is my place some kind of crash pad?

238
00:20:17,280 --> 00:20:18,290
Why are you...

239
00:20:19,550 --> 00:20:22,290
- being so prickly?
- What are you doing here?

240
00:20:25,530 --> 00:20:27,860
- And what happened to your face?
- I asked why you're here.

241
00:20:34,300 --> 00:20:35,440
I felt like I should come...

242
00:20:36,170 --> 00:20:37,370
and say I'm sorry.

243
00:20:42,080 --> 00:20:43,080
What are you sorry for?

244
00:20:44,280 --> 00:20:45,280
For me,

245
00:20:46,710 --> 00:20:49,020
it hasn't been long since Sol and I broke up.

246
00:20:52,090 --> 00:20:53,720
- And...
- Enough.

247
00:20:55,890 --> 00:20:57,460
My feelings are my own problem.

248
00:20:58,290 --> 00:20:59,760
I don't expect anything from you.

249
00:21:03,330 --> 00:21:04,900
So you don't need to say anything else.

250
00:21:07,900 --> 00:21:08,900
Right.

251
00:21:10,700 --> 00:21:11,710
Actually,

252
00:21:12,470 --> 00:21:13,470
there is one thing I want.

253
00:21:15,180 --> 00:21:16,180
What's that?

254
00:21:17,240 --> 00:21:19,110
- I'll do anything I can...
- That internship of yours.

255
00:21:21,620 --> 00:21:22,880
Promise me you'll go back to it.

256
00:21:25,250 --> 00:21:28,360
You said you regret doing nothing for your mom before she passed, yes?

257
00:21:30,690 --> 00:21:32,860
And you know I'm invested in this too, right?

258
00:21:34,560 --> 00:21:36,100
So go back,

259
00:21:36,930 --> 00:21:38,230
and you'd better treat me to something nice.

260
00:21:49,910 --> 00:21:50,910
And...

261
00:21:53,950 --> 00:21:55,950
stop walking on eggshells!

262
00:21:57,320 --> 00:22:00,550
Some people can just up and quit their jobs and act so shameless,

263
