366
00:31:24,580 --> 00:31:26,650
You know what made me really happy today?

367
00:31:26,990 --> 00:31:31,220
Not having to hide us, or worry about what anyone thinks.

368
00:31:31,930 --> 00:31:32,930
Me too.

369
00:31:35,130 --> 00:31:36,160
Ja Yeong.

370
00:31:38,060 --> 00:31:39,230
Can I ask you for a favour?

371
00:31:40,830 --> 00:31:42,570
How about you do me a favour first?

372
00:31:43,170 --> 00:31:45,010
And then I'll do yours.

373
00:31:47,210 --> 00:31:48,210
Deal.

374
00:31:48,980 --> 00:31:50,180
What is it? I'll do it.

375
00:31:51,750 --> 00:31:53,850
Sing a song for me.

376
00:31:54,920 --> 00:31:55,920
What?

377
00:31:56,420 --> 00:31:59,050
No, I can't. I'm a terrible singer. No way.

378
00:31:59,120 --> 00:32:00,120
Then I guess I can't do your favour.

379
00:32:00,190 --> 00:32:01,490
Hey, that's not fair! I mean, come on...

380
00:32:02,160 --> 00:32:03,520
How about I give you a piggyback ride instead?

381
00:32:04,460 --> 00:32:06,790
- No.
- But I'm really terrible at it.

382
00:32:08,500 --> 00:32:09,500
Fine. But don't you laugh.

383
00:32:10,960 --> 00:32:11,970
Now?

384
00:32:13,170 --> 00:32:14,230
Right here?

385
00:32:15,700 --> 00:32:17,340
When and where else?

386
00:32:19,570 --> 00:32:20,570
Don't laugh.

387
00:32:21,240 --> 00:32:22,240
Promise.

388
00:32:22,910 --> 00:32:23,910
Promise.

389
00:32:25,710 --> 00:32:26,750
By my side

390
00:32:29,080 --> 00:32:30,080
Don't laugh.

391
00:32:33,720 --> 00:32:36,120
Just stay

392
00:32:37,990 --> 00:32:40,190
By my side

393
00:32:41,330 --> 00:32:42,700
Don't you ever

394
00:32:44,260 --> 00:32:46,870
Leave me now

395
00:32:52,570 --> 00:32:55,310
I can't leave this longing behind

396
00:32:56,710 --> 00:32:59,610
And travel so far

397
00:33:01,550 --> 00:33:04,220
Just to find

398
00:33:05,390 --> 00:33:09,460
Your rainbow

399
00:34:15,260 --> 00:34:16,720
In the blowing

400
00:34:18,120 --> 00:34:21,030
Cold and biting wind

401
00:34:22,030 --> 00:34:26,730
You may cry from loneliness

402
00:34:29,770 --> 00:34:33,470
But I will always

403
00:34:34,370 --> 00:34:37,680
Stay here by your side

404
00:34:39,480 --> 00:34:44,650
I will never leave

405
00:34:55,960 --> 00:34:57,160
I'm a terrible singer, aren't I?

406
00:34:58,000 --> 00:34:59,000
Not at all.

407
00:35:00,170 --> 00:35:01,230
I loved it.

408
00:35:04,040 --> 00:35:05,040
Really?

409
00:35:07,440 --> 00:35:08,440
So now,

410
00:35:09,010 --> 00:35:11,410
tell me what your favour is. I'll do anything.

411
00:35:13,310 --> 00:35:15,180
Ja Yeong.

412
00:35:17,950 --> 00:35:18,950
The thing is...

413
00:35:21,960 --> 00:35:23,190
Dinner with your family?

414
00:35:25,390 --> 00:35:27,890
If you're pressured, we can wait.

415
00:35:28,560 --> 00:35:30,530
Pressured? Why would I be?

416
00:35:33,430 --> 00:35:34,430
Really?

417
00:35:36,100 --> 00:35:37,640
Then bring Daniel along.

418
00:35:38,470 --> 00:35:40,310
I've already told my dad and Jun Seo about Daniel.

419
00:35:42,680 --> 00:35:44,180
So, if Daniel's okay with it,

420
00:35:45,310 --> 00:35:46,310
let's all meet them together.

421
00:35:46,580 --> 00:35:47,580
Okay.

422
00:36:06,130 --> 00:36:07,630
Thanks for dropping me off.

423
00:36:09,400 --> 00:36:11,870
No, I'm the one who should be thanking you today.

424
00:36:12,810 --> 00:36:14,970
Is that all? Just a "thank you"? Aren't you forgetting something?

425
00:36:28,250 --> 00:36:29,720
Dad?

426
00:36:35,500 --> 00:36:36,500
It's a pleasure to meet you, sir.

427
00:36:36,960 --> 00:36:38,400
Yes. You too.

428
00:36:42,600 --> 00:36:44,470
- Dad.
- Yes?

429
00:36:45,040 --> 00:36:46,970
You should've called first.

430
00:36:49,380 --> 00:36:51,180
I was just leaving a meeting nearby...

431
00:36:51,880 --> 00:36:52,950
and thought I'd stop by.

432
00:36:53,480 --> 00:36:54,480
Okay.

433
00:36:58,490 --> 00:36:59,620
He's a handsome guy.

434
00:37:00,620 --> 00:37:03,490
- He seems like a nice guy too.
- Yes, he is.

435
00:37:04,090 --> 00:37:06,390
- Goodness.
- Oh, no.

436
00:37:11,000 --> 00:37:13,070
- Gosh.
- Here's a napkin.

437
00:37:13,130 --> 00:37:14,130
Thanks.

438
00:37:16,040 --> 00:37:17,300
- I'll get it. Let me.
- Okay.

439
00:37:17,770 --> 00:37:21,540
- He seems like a good kid.
- Yes. Right.

440
00:37:26,580 --> 00:37:27,710
- Well...
- Well...

441
00:37:28,880 --> 00:37:30,950
- Go on, you first.
- No, you go first.

442
00:37:33,290 --> 00:37:35,420
- I'll go first.
- Okay.

443
00:37:37,220 --> 00:37:39,490
Do you want to grab a meal with me and Ja Yeong sometime?

444
00:37:45,030 --> 00:37:46,230
Is this too sudden?

445
00:37:47,770 --> 00:37:49,670
I don't mean to put you on the spot. It's just...

446
00:37:50,900 --> 00:37:51,910
I'd like that.

447
00:37:55,380 --> 00:37:56,380
Let's all have a meal together.

448
00:37:58,580 --> 00:38:00,250
Are you sure?

449
00:38:02,850 --> 00:38:04,420
- Go on in.
- Okay.

450
00:38:04,480 --> 00:38:06,390
- Hey, Jun Kyung.
- Yes?

451
00:38:07,890 --> 00:38:10,390
- Never mind. Go on, go inside.
- Dad...

452
00:38:10,460 --> 00:38:12,830
- Yes, go on in.
- Okay. Get home safe.

453
00:38:12,890 --> 00:38:14,430
- I will.
- Okay.

454
00:38:27,810 --> 00:38:30,010
We have a story from our listener, Midnight.

455
00:38:31,080 --> 00:38:34,150
Late nights at the convenience store where I used to work.

456
00:38:35,010 --> 00:38:36,720
Always around the same time,

457
00:38:37,250 --> 00:38:38,690
always dressed the same,

458
00:38:39,120 --> 00:38:42,560
a customer would come in to buy the exact same beer.

459
00:38:42,620 --> 00:38:43,620
What?

460
00:38:44,460 --> 00:38:45,930
She never said much,

461
00:38:46,460 --> 00:38:47,990
and her face was always blank.

462
00:38:50,060 --> 00:38:51,100
Seeing her like that...

463
00:38:51,500 --> 00:38:54,530
somehow felt like I was looking at myself.

464
00:38:59,770 --> 00:39:02,210
I guess the dead of night is just like that.

465
00:39:03,780 --> 00:39:05,310
A time when you can't hide.

466
00:39:07,050 --> 00:39:08,980
During the day, you can pretend to be happy,

467
00:39:09,380 --> 00:39:10,580
pretend you're not lonely,

468
00:39:11,650 --> 00:39:13,690
whether you're happy or lonely,

469
00:39:14,790 --> 00:39:18,020
you can hide somewhere in between.

470
00:39:21,390 --> 00:39:22,930
But you can't do that in the dead of night.

471
00:39:25,500 --> 00:39:28,800
It tells you that you're not in that gray area.

472
00:39:30,840 --> 00:39:32,840
It's a time that makes things perfectly clear.

473
00:39:36,880 --> 00:39:39,150
- She never asked me anything, - She never asked me anything,

474
00:39:40,650 --> 00:39:42,280
- without saying a word, - without saying a word,

475
00:39:44,880 --> 00:39:46,450
but her presence was a comfort.

476
00:39:49,790 --> 00:39:51,890
For being there with me,

477
00:39:53,490 --> 00:39:56,460
I wanted to thank her for being like me,

478
00:39:58,870 --> 00:39:59,900
but I couldn't.

479
00:40:01,970 --> 00:40:05,070
Then one day, she stopped buying beer at that hour.

480
00:40:10,610 --> 00:40:12,150
I was relieved.

481
00:40:12,210 --> 00:40:14,180
(Police Exam Prep: Criminal law)

482
00:40:14,250 --> 00:40:16,480
It felt like she wasn't lonely anymore.

483
00:40:18,850 --> 00:40:19,990
Thank you.

484
00:40:22,060 --> 00:40:24,190
If we ever happen to meet again,

485
00:40:25,190 --> 00:40:27,330
the next beer is on me.

486
00:40:56,620 --> 00:40:57,660
Gosh.

487
00:41:07,570 --> 00:41:10,270
Didn't you say you felt like none of this mattered anymore?

488
00:41:11,970 --> 00:41:14,510
Yes. That's what I told you.

489
00:41:14,570 --> 00:41:17,180
That was just one week ago.

490
00:41:17,640 --> 00:41:19,280
And now, all of a sudden, it all matters again?

491
00:41:21,510 --> 00:41:23,520
I thought none of it mattered anymore,

492
00:41:24,950 --> 00:41:26,490
but I realised there's still something important to me.

493
00:41:29,960 --> 00:41:33,090
No wonder. I thought you were sentimental for a science student.

494
00:41:35,930 --> 00:41:37,000
I'm sorry.

495
00:41:37,130 --> 00:41:41,630
Aren't you embarrassed? Breaking your word so dramatically?

496
00:41:44,000 --> 00:41:46,510
I am embarrassed. Very.

497
00:41:48,040 --> 00:41:50,040
Does this count as trying?

498
00:41:51,240 --> 00:41:54,780
Gosh, it's so hard to be fair.

499
00:41:55,920 --> 00:41:58,380
Hye On! Did Professor Park Jin Hyung's endorsement come in?

500
00:41:58,520 --> 00:42:01,519
- Yes, I just sent it to print.
- Right. Marketing.

501
00:42:01,520 --> 00:42:03,520
- Yes.
- The writer's interview schedule.

